The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Srinagar , May 16: Police have arrested three of its own men for allegedly having links with militants.          
	Special police officers Farooq Ahmad and Barkat Ali were allegedly working as over-ground workers of the Hizb-ul Mujahideen. Constable Sikander Azam, probably a Lashkar-e-Toiba link, has been arrested in a separate case.                  
	Chennai: M. Karunanidhi was admitted to hospital on Friday with severe neck and back pain, two days after the Tamil Nadu chief minister said he did not wish to celebrate his 85th birthday on June 3. His legs were swollen, too, and doctors at Sri Ramachandra Medical College Hospital advised him to rest for a few days when he went there for a check-up, party sources said.                  
	New York (PTI): A court has pressed hate crime charges against Garrett Green, an American teenager, accused of setting fire to the patka (small turban) of a Sikh student. The 16-year-old did not suffer any major injury.                   
	Midnapore: A Calcutta Municipal Corporation junior engineer was jailed for 10 years on Friday for raping a girl 19 years ago. The district court also asked Sougata Paul to give Rs 1.5 lakh to the victim as compensation. Pal had raped the Class VIII student, who took tuition from his mother, in 1989.                                                                                                                         
